Hi! I created a page to test the script for "Create/test web event". I added "base code" and an event to the page. I specified the link https://ad-test-taupe.vercel.app/test.html , clicked on "go test", but after the transition "Test session" is loading endlessly

It sounds like you're trying to test your event tracking setup. Let's go through a few steps to troubleshoot this issue:

1. **Verify Base Code Placement**: Ensure that the base pixel code is correctly placed in the `<head>` section of your webpage.

2. **Check Event Code**: Make sure the event code is correctly implemented and fires when the intended action occurs on your page.

3. **Test Pixel or Postback**: Use the 'Go test' feature in NewsBreak Ad Manager to verify if both the base code and conversion code are installed correctly.

4. **Network Issues**: Sometimes, network issues can cause loading problems. Try refreshing the page or testing from a different network.

5. **Browser Compatibility**: Ensure that you are using a compatible browser and clear cache if necessary.

If you've checked these and still face issues, please reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com with details of your setup for further assistance.

For more detailed instructions, you can refer to our [Event Tracking Guidelines](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23053537846669-Introduction-to-Multi-Event-Tracking).
Hi! I am trying to add web event, but system shows error "Invalid operation. Please reach out to your Account Manager for more information if it persists. Thank you!"

Hi there! It sounds like you're encountering an "Invalid Operation" error while trying to add a web event. This can happen if there's already an event with the same landing page URL or the same event type and tracking platform under your account. You might want to try using a different landing page URL, a different event type, or create the event under a different account. If you continue to face issues, please reach out to our Ad Support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance. Here's a helpful article that explains more about this error: [Invalid Operation Error during Pixel or Postback Creation](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/27582069096461-Reporting-Conversions-for-CPC-and-CPM-Campaigns).

Currently, events cannot be deleted from the UI. If you need to remove a web event, you may need to reach out to our support team for assistance. Please email adsupport@newsbreak.com with the details of the event you wish to remove, and they will guide you through the process.
Can I add two we event or more?

Yes, you can add multiple web events within one account to test ad performance, build custom audiences, and optimize funnels. Just make sure each event represents a unique action. For example, you can't create two identical events for "complete_payment" within Web events, but you can have one for Web and another for App events. Here's a helpful article on setting up multi-event tracking: [Introduction to Multi-Event Tracking](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23053537846669-Introduction-to-Multi-Event-Tracking).
